qas.question: Where is the eastern terminus of the Trans-Canada Highway?
Outer Ring Road is a another name for what?
What does the divided highway provide?
What is the longest national highway in the world?
What runs through the main part of the city?

context: <a0_0>St. John's<a0_0/> is the eastern terminus of the <b3_0>Trans-Canada Highway<b3_0/>, one of the longest national highways in the world. <a1_0>The divided highway<a1_0/>, also known as <b4_0>"Outer Ring Road"<b4_0/> in the city, runs just outside the main part of the city, with exits to Pitts Memorial Drive, Topsail Road, Team Gushue Highway, Thorburn Road, Allandale Road, Portugal Cove Road and Torbay Road, providing <a2_0>relatively easy access to neighbourhoods<a2_0/> served by those streets. Pitts Memorial Drive runs from Conception Bay South, through the city of Mount Pearl and into downtown St. John's, with interchanges for Goulds, Water Street and Hamilton Avenue-New Gower Street.
